<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12018d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12018d">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12018d"> 18(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Awen = spirit ~ </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: </mm> <blockquote class="sources">Au point de vue psychologique, l&apos;<i>awen</i> repr&eacute;sente, en quelque sorte, le d&eacute;veloppement le plus &eacute;lev&eacute;, la quintessence intellectuelle, la fleur id&eacute;ale de chaque &acirc;me individuelle. Tout homme a son <i>awen</i>, mais il lui est rarement donn&eacute; d&apos;en jouir dans l&apos;existence terrestre. <br><font color="green">[From a psychological perspective, the <i>awen</i> represents, in some manner, the highest level of development, intellectual quintessence, the ideal flower of each individual soul. Every man has his <i>awen</i> but is seldom allowed to enjoy it during his terrestrial existence.]</font> <small> Adolphe Pictet, trad.  <a name="APMB" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#APMB"><cite title="source">Le myst&egrave;re des bardes de l'&icirc;le de Bretagne</cite></a> (1856) 65</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
